OL,3,CCouncil fined #60,000 after pothole
OL,4,Crepair worker suffered vibration injury
OL,6,FThe council failed to report the man's
OL,7,Fdiagnoses, which is a legal obligation.
OL,9,FAn investigation by the Health and
OL,10,FSafety Executive (HSE) found that
OL,11,Fother employees continued to work with
OL,12,Fvibrating tools after being diagnosed.
OL,14,FKate Harney, enforcement lawyer for
OL,15,Fthe HSE, said: "Rotherham Council had
OL,16,Fbeen exposing employees to the risks
OL,17,Farising from the use of vibrating
OL,18,Ftools for a significant period of time.
